==English==
{{wikipedia|pearls before swine}}

===Etymology===
From the {{m|en|Bible}} "Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither '''cast ye your pearls before swine''', lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you." – {{l|en|KJV}}, [[s:Bible_(King_James)/Matthew#7:6|''Matthew 7:6'']].

