===Verb===
{{en-verb|cast<,,cast> pearls before swine}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[give]] [[thing]]s of [[value]] to [[those]] who will not [[understand]] or [[appreciate]] them.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1947|author={{w|Tennessee Williams}}|title={{w|A Streetcar Named Desire}}|section=Scene 10|text=''Blanche:'' ...Physical beauty is passing. A transitory possession. But beauty of the mind and richness of the spirit and tenderness of the heart—and I have all of those things—aren't taken away, but grow! Increase with the years! How strange that I should be called a destitute woman! When I have all of these treasures locked in my heart. ''[A choked sob comes from her]'' I think of myself as a very, very rich woman! But I have been foolish—'''casting my pearls before swine'''!}}

